My 60 has a 68 IRS rear setup in it. PO handled the install and it looks
factory correct. All of the parts are inexpensive junkyard bounty, but I
hear the labor time was pretty impressive.

If you'd rather do a kit, I'd recommend CE as a high-quality alternative
to Shadetree Welding 101.

